InclusionRules.name: Controlled CVD: <=2 conditions AND <=2 procedures
InclusionRules.description:
QC Note: This is a little complicated. Among those with CVD, we want to stratify by controlled vs. uncontrolled. This cohort defines the controlled group who have at least one CVD-related diagnosis or procedure and who have a maximum of two procedures and a maximum of two diagnoses.  It is important that this strata does not overlap the definition for uncontrolled CVD.  That cohort will include people who have more than two procedures or more than two diagnoses.

QC Note: Does my use of "using distinct" seem appropriate?  My understanding (based on scanning the SQL code in the export tab) is that this will not count multiple instances of the same SNOMED concept within the look-back. I would have preferred to count twice when the same diagnosis occurs on two different days but I don't know if that's possible.
